items.title: “Seifeddine Makhlouf’s forced return is a violation of the principle of non-refoulement. By handing him over to Tunisian authorities without allowing him any opportunity to contest the decision or assessing the risks he faces in Tunisia, including the risk of prolonged arbitrary detention and unfair trial, Algeria has breached its obligations under international human rights law, including the Refugee Convention,”
